Package: smoltEASE
Type: Package
Title: Applying EASE uncertainty within SCRAPI smolt estimates
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Smith", email = "david.smith@idfg.idaho.gov", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Thomas", "Delomas", role = "ctb")
)
Maintainer: David Smith <david.smith@idfg.idaho.gov>
Description: Tools for estimating juvenile salmonid escapement at Lower Granite Dam
    using extensions of the SCRAPI framework. The package implements SCRAPI2,
    which propagates uncertainty in guidance efficiency (GE) and genetic stock
    identification (GSI) through bootstrap estimation. It includes utilities
    for preparing PIT tag data, fitting Bayesian hierarchical models for GE,
    generating posterior draws, and integrating these into escapement estimates.
    Designed to align with EASE-style uncertainty propagation used in adult
    escapement analyses.
Imports:
    dplyr,
    readr,
    tibble,
    tidyr,
    Hmisc,
    stats
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/dsmi313/smoltEASE
BugReports: https://github.com/dsmi313/smoltEASE/issues
